paragraphs.text:
%md

 Output of ZeroAndDifferences.jar for 1x^3 (see video for algorithm explanation https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H4dBkofVA4A) is represented by graph.jpg (last paragraph).  Each node has a property representing the differenced polynomial.  This polynomial has another property representing the number of rational roots the differenced polynomial has. The location on the graph, which depth level, indicates the number of rational roots necessary for the polynomial to be determined.  For example the graph root is a node with a constant and thus no expected rational roots.  The first level is a linear expecting 1 rational root. The second a quadratic with two expected roots...  The classification model takes the node's polynomial number of roots and its level as parameters and predicts if it is determined or not.  Note though the prediction model does not yet accept a GraphSage embedding as feature properties.

paragraphs.title: GraphSage training model (embedding not currently useful for label prediction).
paragraphs.text:
CALL gds.beta.graphSage.train(
  'myGraph',
  {
     modelName: 'myGraphh',
     epochs:75
    , aggregator: 'pool'
 //   , aggregator: 'mean'
    , activationFunction: 'relu'
    , featureProperties: ['determined','zero','one','two','three']
    , projectedFeatureDimension: 5
    , sampleSizes: [25, 10]
    , searchDepth: 5
    , learningRate:.05
  }
)

paragraphs.title: Select feater properties (GraphSage embeddings or projected graph node featers) and train model.
paragraphs.text:
CALL gds.alpha.ml.nodeClassification.train('myGraph', {
  nodeLabels: ['Dnode'],
  modelName: 'determined-model',
//  featureProperties: ['embeddings'],                                      //  not working. maybe also a wNum0,wNum1 one hot.
  featureProperties: ['zero','one','two','three','wNum','totalZero'],     //  works well
//  featureProperties: ['wNum','totalZero'],                                  //  not at all convincing...
  targetProperty: 'determined',
  randomSeed: 49,
  holdoutFraction: 0.2,
  validationFolds: 185,
  metrics: [ 'F1_WEIGHTED' ],
  params: [
    {penalty: 0.0625},
    {penalty: 0.5},
    {penalty: 1.0},
    {penalty: 4.0}
  ]
}) YIELD modelInfo
RETURN
  {penalty: modelInfo.bestParameters.penalty} AS winningModel,
  modelInfo.metrics.F1_WEIGHTED.outerTrain AS trainGraphScore,
  modelInfo.metrics.F1_WEIGHTED.test AS testGraphScore

paragraphs.title: Write 0 predicted un-determined 1 predicted determined in Dnode predictedDetermined property.

Blue nodes are correctly predicted as determind (number of  rational roots = degree of polynomial).  Green nodes are correctly predicted as under determined (number of ratonal roots < degree of polynomial).   Red node was incorrectly predicted as determined.
